Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition, which are subfields of CL.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on acoustic modeling for speech recognition.
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with processing audio signals for speech recognition.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes novel techniques for improving the performance of an end-to-end machine learning model.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper deals with developing an AI system for speech recognition.
